1. Terraform Installation
-----------------

https://www.terraform.io/downloads

1. curl -fsSL https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com/gpg | sudo apt-key add -
2. sudo apt-add-repository "deb [arch=amd64] https://apt.releases.hashicorp.com $(lsb_release -cs) main"
3. sudo apt-get update && sudo apt-get install terraform
4. terraform -v

2. Clone your repo and go to the file where you have your terraform scripts

# terraform fmt
# terraform init
# terraform plan
# terraform apply

3. After EKS Cluster setup, run the bellow commands 
 Verify config file is available or not 
 # rm ~/.kube/config

 # aws eks --region us-east-1 update-kubeconfig --name eks --profile terraform 

 After that we can access our Kubernetes cluster.
 # kubectl get svc